ent and free from bias,28\r\n17,GENERATIVE AI,BIAS,\"Generative AI tools may introduce bias into content, reflecting the biases present in their training data\",28\r\n223,MANUSCRIPT,COPY-EDITING,Copy-editing is a stage in manuscript preparation that may involve the use of AI tools,28\r\n169,EDITOR,RESEARCH DESIGN,Editors must evaluate whether the use of AI tools has affected the research design in a way that compromises integrity,28\r\n18,GENERATIVE AI,HALLUCINATION,\"Generative AI tools may generate content that is not factually accurate, leading to hallucinations that are difficult to identify\",27\r\n16,GENERATIVE AI,INACCURACY,\"Generative AI tools can produce inaccurate content due to their statistical nature, making it hard to detect and correct errors\",27\r\n80,LANGUAGE MODEL,LLM,\"The term \"\"LLM\"\" stands for \"\"language model,\"\" and it refers to systems such as ChatGPT, which are a specific type of artificial intelligence technology designed for text generation. LLMs are categorized under the broader umbrella of language models, representing advanced AI systems capable of understanding and producing human-like text. These models are widely used in various applications, including but not limited to chatbots, content creation, and natural language processing tasks. The distinction between \"\"language model\"\" and \"\"LLM\"\" is primarily one of scope, with \"\"LLM\"\" often denoting large-scale, deep learning-based language models that have been trained on vast amounts of text data. Both terms are frequently used interchangeably in academic and technical contexts, though \"\"LLM\"\" typically implies a more sophisticated and data-intensive approach to language modeling.\",27\r\n87,LANGUAGE MODEL,COMPLIANCE,Language models must be used in compliance with AI policies,27\r\n210,JOURNAL,RESEARCH DESIGN,Journals must evaluate whether the use of AI tools has affected the research design in a way that compromises integrity,27\r\n78,LANGUAGE MODEL,PUBLISHER,Publishers must ensure that language models used in manuscript preparation do not compromise originality or integrity,26\r\n99,LLM,DATA,LLMs can generate data that is used for analysis in academic papers,23\r\n409,DATA,DE GRUYTER BRILL,\"De Gruyter Brill advises authors to handle data responsibly when using AI tools, ensuring it is not used inappropriately or without proper disclosure\",22\r\n410,DATA,EMERALD,\"Emerald prohibits the use of generative AI tools to manipulate or report research data, ensuring its authenticity and integrity\",22\r\n411,DATA,TAYLOR & FRANCIS,Taylor & Francis emphasizes the importance of maintaining the integrity of research data and prohibits the use of Generative AI to generate synthetic data without proper methodology,22\r\n81,LANGUAGE MODEL,MANUSCRIPT PREPARATION,\"The use of **LANGUAGE MODEL** in the process of **MANUSCRIPT PREPARATION** is highlighted, as these models are employed to support the creation and refinement of academic manuscripts. Specifically, **LANGUAGE MODEL** may assist in enhancing the linguistic quality of manuscripts, contributing to clearer and more polished written communication. This integration reflects the growing role of artificial intelligence in academic writing processes, where language models serve as tools to improve the overall coherence and readability of scholarly work. The relationship between **LANGUAGE MODEL** and **MANUSCRIPT PREPARATION** underscores the intersection of AI technologies and academic publishing, emphasizing the potential for automation and enhancement in scholarly communication.\",22\r\n415,RESEARCH DESIGN,TAYLOR & FRANCIS,Taylor & Francis requires human oversight in research design to ensure that Generative AI does not replace core researcher responsibilities,22\r\n389,PUBLISHER,ALGORITHM,Publishers must ensure that algorithms used in AI tools are transparent and free from bias,20\r\n388,PUBLISHER,BIAS,Publishers must monitor and address biases in AI systems used during the publication process,18\r\n414,RESEARCH DESIGN,TOOL,\"Research design may involve the use of tools, including AI-based ones, for ideation and planning\",12\r\n413,ALGORITHM,\"AI TECHNOLOGY(\"\"ENTITY\"\"\",algorithm,7\r\n\nOutput:", "parameters": {"model": "qwen-turbo", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": 0.0, "presence_penalty": 0.0, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 2000, "n": 1}, "history": null}